          <p><i>"Some people lose their sense of proportion, I have lost my sense of Scale"</i> - Will Self</p>

          <h3>The Little Book of Scale</h3>
          <p>If the Sun is the size of a Grapefruit, the Earth is a grain of sand, and the distance between the two is a London bus.</p>

          <p>Scale is intriguing. Scale is everywhere. Scale is our experience of the world. The human scale is the 1:1, the point of reference. Everything is designed around it. Wealth is an example of scale, so is a sculpture, a building, a planet or a molecule.</p>

          <p>Scale is a universal and timeless subject. It's a BIG subject. We aim to celebrate it and distil facts to fit our little book without losing their strength.</p>


